CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 14, 1959 reads: "Wall Collapses - The eastern wall of Grob's Tavern at 2150 Wylie Ave., collapsed about 4:30 pm tuesday, but nobody was injured. Maurice Grob, the owner, says of fire, which destroyed the next-door building in November, left the Grob structure without support on that side of the building.  No estimate was placed on the damage, but the tavern is not operation.  Patrolman Johnny Daniels is shown doing guard duty, while an unidentified spectator looks on." -- Harris Photo
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Grob's Tavern with collapsed wall, side view, with exposed interior overhead light fixture, and view of Williams Barber Shop, street no. 2149 across street
